Product Vision Document

Project Title: University Clinic Appointment System
SDG Supported: SDG 3 – Good Health and Well-Being

1. Project Idea

The University Clinic Appointment System is a software solution designed to help students book medical appointments online. Instead of waiting in long queues at the university clinic, students can use the system to schedule appointments with doctors quickly and efficiently.

2. Problem Statement

Many university clinics use manual booking systems which can cause long waiting times and confusion about doctor availability. Students may also struggle to track their appointment status.

3. Proposed Solution

The proposed system will allow students to view doctor availability, book appointments, and manage their medical visits digitally. Doctors will be able to view and manage appointments while administrators will manage users and clinic schedules.

4. Target Users

Students

Doctors

Clinic Administrators

5. System Goals

The goals of this system are:

Reduce waiting time at the clinic

Improve appointment management

Provide easy access to healthcare services for students

Improve efficiency of clinic operations
